way. Serve these pancakes hot off the skillet, with dipping sauce. They make a great appetizer on their own, or a lovely accompaniment to soups, curries, or stir fries. Enjoy!%0a%3c %0a%3c !! Ingredients%0a%3c %0a%3c !!! Pancakes:%0a%3c * 1 cup whole spelt flour (optional, use white flour if you prefer)%0a%3c * 1 1/2 cup unbleached white flour%0a%3c * 1/2 cup boiling water%0a%3c * 1/2 cup cold water%0a%3c * 1/2 tbsp. baking powder%0a%3c * 1 tsp. sea salt%0a%3c * 1/4 cup toasted sesame seed oil%0a%3c * 2 cups finely chopped garlic scapes%0a%3c %0a%3c !!! Dipping Sauce:%0a%3c * 3 tbsp. organic soy or tamari sauce%0a%3c * 3 tbsp. rice vinegar%0a%3c * 1 to 2 tsp. freshly grated ginger%0a%3c * 1 tsp. sesame oil%0a%3c * 1 tsp. sugar or honey%0a%3c * A pinch of dried chili flakes (optional)%0a%3c %0a%3c !!! For frying:%0a%3c * About 1/4 cup grapeseed or peanut oil%0a%3c %0a%3c !! Directions%0a%3c %0a%3c # Mix the spelt and white flours together with the salt. Put half of the mixture in one bowl and half in another bowl.%0a%3c # In one bowl add 1/2 cup boiling water. Mix with a wooden spoon until the dough can handled. Knead for 2 minutes in the bowl.%0a%3c # In the other bowl, mix the baking powder into the flour. Add the cold water and mix with a wooden spoon until dough can be handled. Knead for 2 minutes in the bowl.%0a%3c # Incorporate both doughs together by kneading them into one another for 5 minutes on a lightly floured surface. This dough is very forgiving. If its too dry, simply add a bit of water. If it's too sticky, simply add a bit of flour. The dough should feel nice and moist but not stick to your hands.%0a%3c # Shape into a ball, and place in a bowl with a damp towel on top and let it rest at room temperature for 1 to 2 hours.%0a%3c # Cut the dough into 4 pieces.%0a%3c # Roll each one into a thin 9 or 10 inch circle.%0a%3c # Brush with one tablespoon of sesame oil and sprinkle with about 1/2 cup of garlic scapes, evenly distributed over the surface.%0a%3c # Roll the dough into a tight cylinder and pinch in the edges to seal. Coil this cylinder into a spiral and tuck in the end. Flatten it into a disc with the palm of your hand. Roll this out into a flat pancake, about 1/4 inch thick. Repeat with the remaining pieces of dough. Let the 4 pancakes rest for about 10 minutes before frying.%0a%3c # Meanwhile, make the dipping sauce by whisking all ingredients together.%0a%3c # Heat about 1 tablespoon of oil in a heavy skillet on medium heat. When the oil is hot, gently place the pancake into the pan and cook on each side for about 2 to 3 minutes or until nice and golden. Repeat with remaining pancakes. Cut the pancakes into wedges and serve hot, with the dipping sauce.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c !! Tips/Techniques%0a%3c %0a%3c If you wish to keep your pancakes warm, place them on a baking sheet in a 200 F oven. However, they are best when served straight off the skillet.%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c http://www.pbs.org/food/wp-content/blogs.dir/2/files/2013/06/Aube-Giroux-169x215.jpg''Aube Giroux is a food writer and filmmaker who shares her love of cooking on her farm-to-table blog, [[http://kitchenvignettes.blogspot.com/ | Kitchen Vignettes]].''%0a%3c %0a%3c ''Aube is a passionate organic gardener and home cook who likes to share the stories of how food gets to our dinner plates. Her work has been shown on television and at international film festivals. In 2012, she was the recipient of Saveur Magazine’s Best Food Blog award in the video category.''%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:linkwikiwords:)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>comment%3c%3c%0a%3c Summary: Try this garlic scape pancakes recipe from Kitchen Vignettes. These flaky pancakes are a great appetizer or side dish from PBS Food.%0a%3c Tags: saved page, garlic, scapes, pancakes%0a%3c (:tags-hide saved page, garlic, scapes, pancakes:)%0a%3c (:title Garlic Scape Pancakes Recipe | Kitchen Vignettes | PBS Food:)%0a%3c Source: http://www.pbs.org/food/kitchen-vignettes/garlic-scape-pancakes/%0a%3c Paren